Hotel
Job Level
Management
Primary Objective of the position
Under the guidance of the General Manager assess, evaluate and ensure that long-term and short-term goals of Food & Drinks operations are met. To direct and manage all Food & Drinks activities to maximise revenue, profitability and quality goals by developing and executing marketing strategies, up-selling strategies, controlling costs, and by providing quality service to guests. All work will be in line with the hotel’s guidelines and business plan and the Carlson Rezidor Hotel Group’s corporate guidelines and service concepts.
Tasks, Duties and Responsibilities – Assess, Evaluate and Ensure Food & Drinks goals are met
• Develop, implement and evaluate the hotel’s marketing plan, general business plan, marketing and sales strategies to ensure optimum guest satisfaction, sales maximisation and profitability.
• Responsible for all food and drinks activities, including conference and banqueting
• Manage, motivate and organise the department
• Develop food and drinks concepts
• Determine needs for training and implement training within own department
• Monitors present and future trends, practices and systems in the food & drink industry to ensure that the hotel’s F&D; operations are competitive in the market place.
• Participates in development of recognition programmes for employees.
• Randomly inspects all F&D; regions to ensure facilities and equipment are clean, well maintained and replaced if necessary.
• Check F&D; outlet reservation list, hotel arrival list, conference guest list, and VIP list and ensure that all the F&D; employees are aware of VIP guests.
• Challenge employees within department to achieve optimum food cost percentage and service per employee.
• Controls and analyses departmental cost on an ongoing basis and take action to control negative deviation.
• Audit F&D; service and quality on regular basis and develop and implement strategies to improve results.
• Plan and co-ordinate in-house activities and package plans with Executive Chef and Director of Sales & Marketing.
Requirements
• Fluency in English, both written and oral
• Experience from a similar position or equivalent
• Relevant business education
• Result oriented individual who gets things done
• Strong interpersonal skills
• Highly motivated, enthusiastic and innovative
• Outgoing, dynamic and sales focused
• Business oriented and a natural attitude towards providing excellent quality service
